			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Veksar and Droga are great examples of how older expansions can have content either updated or added.  While I realize that you need to keep some lower-level content intact for new players, just the original lands of EQ alone have enough dungeons that a few of them could be picked for revamp, ie Najena, SolA, etc.
<br />

<br />
When I look at the current state of affairs on my own server (Tarew Marr) I have to wonder how the playerbase will look in a year.  GoD alone caused most of the top end guilds to take a significant hit to their ranks as players realized just what it would mean in terms of time committment, boredom and struggling with shitty design and bugs to advance in this expansion.  That has caused many of the elemental tiered guilds to collapse as these guilds carry out mass recruiting and players consolidate to the top 4 or 5 guilds on the server.
<br />
We just had a 5th guild on the server gain access to plane of time, but beyond that there isn't anyone even remotely close.  The gap between the casual gamers and top end guilds is, as mentioned, growing enormous with every sign pointing to this gap becoming much wider in the future.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
